# @VERSION spec:gdls v:0.1.0 generated:2026-03-31 source:schema-agent
# @FORMAT COLUMN|SQL_TYPE|NULLABLE|KEY|DESCRIPTION
# Project Atlas — migration 0003: idempotency keys (Mar 31)

@D atlas_finance|Idempotency table introduced for posting consumers

@T IdempotencyKey|Per-event idempotency keys to prevent double-posts on consumer rebalance
key|VARCHAR(120)|N|PK|Idempotency key (typically Kafka topic + offset)
seen_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||When the event was first observed
entry_id|UUID|Y|FK|Resulting journal entry, if posted
expires_at|TIMESTAMPTZ|N||Retention horizon (default +7 days)
# Note: entry_id is a logical FK to JournalEntry.entry_id (defined in m0001-initial.gdls)
